---
title: "_multiCall (Caller)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_validate: check calls.length
    q_validate --> q_revert_empty: calls.length == 0
    q_revert_empty --> [*]: revert Errors.EmptyList()
    q_validate --> q_init_array: calls.length > 0
    q_init_array --> q_iter: returnData = new bytes[](calls.length); i = 0
    q_iter --> q_call: i < calls.length
    q_call --> q_store: returnData[i] = _call(calls[i].target, calls[i].data)
    q_store --> q_iter: i = i + 1
    q_iter --> q_return: i >= calls.length
    q_return --> [*]: return returnData

    note right of q_iter
        INV-001: calls array must be non-empty or execution reverts
        INV-002: each call is executed sequentially via _call
        INV-003: if any individual _call reverts, the entire _multiCall reverts
        INV-004: returnData.length == calls.length on successful completion
        INV-005: 0 <= i <= calls.length at every iteration entry
    end note
